{
  "card_id": "next_day_model",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "Next Day Model",
  "aliases": [
    "day-after trading model",
    "Day-After Trading Model",
    "next candle model",
    "Next Candle Model",
    "next day",
    "Next Day",
    "Next Day Expectation",
    "next day expectation",
    "NMXM Model",
    "nmxm model"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A fractal bias framework predicting the next candle's direction based on the current candle's close relative to the prior candle's range or after tagging a higher-timeframe PD array. A close inside the prior range (often after failing to displace beyond it) signals reversal toward the opposite side; a close outside signals continuation. When price reaches into a PD array and closes back away, the next candle moves in that closing direction. Applicable across all timeframes.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Identify the previous candle's high-low range and any relevant higher-timeframe PD arrays (e.g., fair value gap, order block) or swing points at that level.",
    "If the current candle closes inside the previous candle's range (often after attempting to displace beyond its high/low or swing point), anticipate a reversal: next candle moves toward the opposite range extreme (previous low if at high, or previous high if at low).",
    "If the current candle closes outside the previous candle's range (above high or below low), anticipate continuation in the direction of the close.",
    "If the current candle reaches into a higher-timeframe PD array and closes back away from it (respects it), anticipate the next candle to move in the closing direction, targeting opposing draw on liquidity (e.g., previous day low).",
    "After establishing the directional bias, drop to a lower timeframe to confirm via a change in state of delivery or phases of price delivery, avoiding signals in choppy/consolidation conditions.",
    "Apply across all timeframes.",
    "In daily chart, observe if previous day sweeps swing high/low or PD array and closes back inside the range; if so, expect next day to be bearish (after sweep high) or bullish (after sweep low).",
    "Mark previous day high/low as next day's draw on liquidity target.",
    "During kill zones (Asian, London, NY AM), wait for displacement and liquidity sweep toward opposite side before entering at discount or OTE zone."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Establishes bias for the next candle/session: reversal closes inside prior range signal moves toward opposite extreme; continuation closes outside signal trend continuation; PD array respects signal movement away from array toward opposing liquidity. Use to set targets (e.g., previous day high/low) and align entries across timeframes. Confirm with lower timeframe change in state of delivery or order block entries. Typical risk-reward 2R to 3:1.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Expecting the model to be 100% accurate; signals can fail, especially on lower timeframes, requiring additional confirmation.",
    "Using the model on excessively low timeframes where price action noise reduces reliability.",
    "Taking directional bias from a PD array reaction without first confirming a change in state of delivery on a lower timeframe.",
    "Ignoring that the prior candle must actually engage and respect a valid higher-timeframe PD array to generate the signal.",
    "Applying the model mechanically without considering phases of price delivery, leading to trades against strong trends or in consolidation.",
    "Acting on conflicting signals (e.g., close inside range after a sweep of a swing point) without waiting for further price action to clarify.",
    "Forcing a directional bias when both sides of the range have been taken and no clear displacement has occurred.",
    "Applying the model when price sweeps high/low but fails to close back inside the range (must close inside).",
    "Entering prematurely on small displacement in Asian/London session instead of waiting for NY AM session confirmation.",
    "Continuing to trade in the same bias after price has reached the draw on liquidity target without reassessment.",
    "Using the model in isolation without higher timeframe top-down analysis."
  ],
